1386–1416","1343–1376":"1343–1376","1345–1398":"1345–1398","29 May 1376":"29 May 1376","1382":"1382","1367":"1367","1345":"1345","1388":"1388","1454":"1454","1398":"1398","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","1453":"1453","1365":"1365","1386":"1386","9 September 1388":"9 September 1388","about 1385":"about 1385","1416":"1416","Hassop, Derbyshire, England":"Hassop, Derbyshire, England","Darley Dale, Derbyshire, England":"Darley Dale, Derbyshire, England","Bakewell, Derbyshire, England":"Bakewell, Derbyshire, England","Tideswell, Derbyshire, England":"Tideswell, Derbyshire, England","Hassop, Derby, England":"Hassop, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Foljambe","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English: nickname from Old French  <i>fol</i> ‘foolish, silly’ +  <i>jambe</i> ‘leg’, probably a nickname for a lame person, someone with a maimed or crooked leg;  compare  Belgian  . In Old French  <i>fol</i> could be used of something useless or of little value, e.g.  <i>farine folle</i> ‘mill dust’."],"variants":[{"name":"Fulljames","meanings":["English: variant of   Foljambe   with post-medieval excrescent  <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Belgian","meanings":["Norman, English, Scottish: nickname from Anglo-Norman French  <i>bele jambe</i> ‘fine leg’."]}]},{"name":"Godfrey","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old French name <i>Godefroy</i>, which is of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>god</i> ‘god’ (or <i>gōd</i> ‘good’) + <i>fred</i>, <i>frid</i> ‘peace’. This was adopted by the Normans, and brought to England by immigrants from the Low Countries and France. It was borne by a Norman saint (  <i>c.</i>1066–1115 ) who became bishop of Amiens. There has been considerable confusion with   Geoffrey ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":15,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Godfrey Foljambe III was born in 1367, in Hassop, Derbyshire, England, his father, Godfrey de Foljambe II, was 24 and his mother, Margaret de Villiers, was 23. He married Margaret Leeke about 1385, in Tideswell, Derbyshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 9 September 1388, in Bakewell, Derbyshire, England, at the age of 21, and was buried in Bakewell, Derbyshire, England."},"et":{"1367–9 September 1388":"1367–9. september 1388","1365–1453":"1365–1453","1367–1388":"1367–1388","1367–1454":"1367–1454","1386–1416":"1386–1416","1343–1376":"1343–1376","1345–1398":"1345–1398","29 May 1376":"29. mai 1376","1382":"1382","1367":"1367","1345":"1345","1388":"1388","1454":"1454","1398":"1398","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","1453":"1453","1365":"1365","1386":"1386","9 September 1388":"9. september 1388","about 1385":"umbes 1385","1416":"1416","Hassop, Derbyshire, England":"Hassop, Derbyshire, England","Darley Dale, Derbyshire, England":"Darley Dale, Derbyshire, England","Bakewell, Derbyshire, England":"Bakewell, Derbyshire, England","Tideswell, Derbyshire, England":"Tideswell, Derbyshire, England","Hassop, Derby, England":"Hassop, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1367–9 September 1388":"1367–9. syyskuuta 1388","1365–1453":"1365–1453","1367–1388":"1367–1388","1367–1454":"1367–1454","1386–1416":"1386–1416","1343–1376":"1343–1376","1345–1398":"1345–1398","29 May 1376":"29. toukokuuta 1376","1382":"1382","1367":"1367","1345":"1345","1388":"1388","1454":"1454","1398":"1398","1376":"1376","1343":"134